    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I've just rewritten our GL bindings, so it is now at least theoretically possible to fix this.  It's not a priority for me, however, because it only affects a subset of people running Windows (see [remark](https://wiki.libsdl.org/SDL_GL_GetProcAddress)), and I have no way to test any changes regarding this.\n\nThe fix I have in mind would be to compare the [current context](https://wiki.libsdl.org/SDL_GL_GetCurrentContext) with the context that the entry points were queried from, and then reinit all the bindings if they differ.  Of course, this won't help if the driver dies in the middle of rendering a frame, but nothing will help you there.\n"
